00:18:43,239 --> 00:18:44,324
Come on!

240
00:18:49,161 --> 00:18:51,288
What about sharks?

241
00:18:52,873 --> 00:18:55,459
You ever see any sharks while you're

242
00:18:55,542 --> 00:18:57,627
scuba-ing or whatever?

243
00:18:57,669 --> 00:19:00,255
I've never gone scuba diving
in my whole life.

244
00:19:01,631 --> 00:19:04,967
- You lied in your essay?
- No. I made it up.

245
00:19:05,009 --> 00:19:07,220
It's different from lying.

246
00:19:08,679 --> 00:19:11,765
Those drawings you make,
you seen those things yourself?

247
00:19:12,641 --> 00:19:14,476
No, but...

248
00:19:18,855 --> 00:19:20,357
Hey! Look at that!

249
00:19:20,732 --> 00:19:22,609
- Cool!
- That's been there forever.

250
00:19:22,650 --> 00:19:23,985
I wouldn't trust it.

251
00:19:24,736 --> 00:19:26,529
Come on. Just try it.

252
00:19:28,823 --> 00:19:30,241
OK.

253
00:19:36,538 --> 00:19:38,623
You got it? That's it.

254
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:41,459
Thanks.

255
00:19:44,170 --> 00:19:46,839
- What are you doing?
- Getting up higher.

256
00:19:48,716 --> 00:19:49,967
OK.

257
00:19:57,849 --> 00:20:00,977
Wow! That was so much fun.
You have to try it. Come on.

258
00:20:21,538 --> 00:20:22,956
OK.

259
00:20:39,888 --> 00:20:41,931
Let your head hang back,
watch the clouds.

260
00:20:41,973 --> 00:20:43,766
Feels like flying.

261
00:21:09,123 --> 00:21:13,001
- We need a place. Just for us.
- Hmm?

262
00:21:13,127 --> 00:21:15,921
Where there's no
Janice Averys or Scott Hoagers.

263
00:21:16,004 --> 00:21:19,674
Yeah, but when we go back to school,
there they are waiting.

264
00:21:19,758 --> 00:21:21,342
Yeah, but...

265
00:21:21,426 --> 00:21:24,470
...someplace better than
just not being at school.

266
00:21:25,138 --> 00:21:27,932
What if there was a magical kingdom
only we knew about?

267
00:21:29,058 --> 00:21:30,684
I don't know. What if?

268
00:21:30,768 --> 00:21:32,895
OK, well...

269
00:21:32,978 --> 00:21:35,564
...what if the only way
we could enter it

270
00:21:35,606 --> 00:21:37,858
is by swinging on this enchanted rope?

271
00:21:37,941 --> 00:21:40,777
- Enchanted rope?
- Yeah.

272
00:21:41,653 --> 00:21:43,238
Come on.

273
00:21:48,242 --> 00:21:50,202
Leslie!

274
00:21:51,495 --> 00:21:52,496
Leslie!

275
00:22:03,006 --> 00:22:04,674
Leslie.

276
00:22:09,678 --> 00:22:11,930
- Come on!
- Wait up.

277
00:22:40,332 --> 00:22:41,791
Ahh!

278
00:22:41,875 --> 00:22:44,335
We shouldn't be in here.
This isn't our land.

279
00:22:44,377 --> 00:22:47,338
- Not so loud. They'll hear you.
- What are you talking about?

280
00:22:53,927 --> 00:22:56,013
Hey! What's that?

281
00:22:58,014 --> 00:23:01,434
Whoa. Jess, look at this. Wow.

282
00:23:03,811 --> 00:23:07,106
Too bad for them.
They got so close.

283
00:23:07,189 --> 00:23:10,234
- What are you talking about?
- To the kingdom.

284
00:23:12,444 --> 00:23:14,947
- What's that?
- What?

285
00:23:15,030 --> 00:23:18,116
That sound. I've heard it before.
Someone's out there.

286
00:23:18,158 --> 00:23:21,036
That's the sound of the prisoners
rattling their chains.

287
00:23:21,828 --> 00:23:23,621
What prisoners?

288
00:23:23,705 --> 00:23:26,040
The prisoners of the Dark Master.

289
00:23:29,835 --> 00:23:32,629
- We should go.
- Wait, Jess, look.

290
00:23:33,922 --> 00:23:35,465
What is it?

291
00:23:39,469 --> 00:23:40,970
Look at this.

292
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:50,604
Wow. This is amazing.

293
00:23:54,775 --> 00:23:55,943
Wow.

294
00:24:07,286 --> 00:24:08,204
This is it.

295
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:25,344
Warriors.

296
00:24:27,013 --> 00:24:30,724
- Try dragonflies.
- No. They're warriors.

297
00:24:30,808 --> 00:24:33,018
From the treetop provinces.

298
00:24:34,144 --> 00:24:38,231
- I don't know this game.
- What game? This is for real.

299
00:24:40,525 --> 00:24:44,195
This is the ruins
of a once great fortress

300
00:24:44,237 --> 00:24:46,614
whose people have been imprisoned.

301
00:24:48,657 --> 00:24:51,493
Jess, you and I have been
sent to free them.

302
00:24:53,579 --> 00:24:56,790
Prisoners of the Dark Master, hear me!

303
00:24:57,374 --> 00:25:00,043
We have come to free you.

304
00:25:00,126 --> 00:25:01,711
Do you hear us?

305
00:25:01,795 --> 00:25:03,671
Show me that you hear us!

306
00:25:11,345 --> 00:25:14,640
You got lucky timing. The wind's
been blowing off and on all day.

307
00:25:16,391 --> 00:25:20,895
Can't hear you!

308
00:25:54,176 --> 00:25:57,137
- Go straight home. I'll see you soon.
- OK. See ya!

309
00:27:18,962 --> 00:27:21,548
Hey, don't you think
we should give her a hand?

310
00:27:24,676 --> 00:27:26,177
Uh... She's... She's fine.

311
00:27:26,677 --> 00:27:29,055
Beep, beep, beep, beep.

312
00:27:29,138 --> 00:27:30,764
...forget. There are four of us.

313
00:27:30,806 --> 00:27:32,057
OK.

314
00:27:33,934 --> 00:27:35,811
Remember to bring your bag.

315
00:27:35,894 --> 00:27:38,313
Why would anyone
want to wear that?

316
00:27:43,693 --> 00:27:45,069
Janice!

317
00:27:45,153 --> 00:27:46,696
- You OK?
- What's the problem?

318
00:27:46,779 --> 00:27:49,448
- Jess Aarons tripped me.
- Uh...

319
00:27:49,490 --> 00:27:51,450
On purpose.

320
00:27:51,533 --> 00:27:54,036
OK, Aarons. Hit the road.

321
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:57,330
- But he didn't do anything.
- Go.

322
00:27:57,372 --> 00:28:01,000
- It was definitely him.
- I know.

323
00:28:15,764 --> 00:28:19,726
- What happened to you?
- Janice is a very talented person.

324
00:28:19,809 --> 00:28:22,520
She can shoot ketchup packets
over four rows of seats.

325
00:28:22,604 --> 00:28:24,272
Jeez.

326
00:28:24,689 --> 00:28:27,650
Can I wash up at your house?
My mom sees this, she'll be all over

327
00:28:27,692 --> 00:28:30,236
the principal and everybody,
and my life will be over.

328
00:28:33,113 --> 00:28:36,074
Why would Dad do this?

329
00:28:36,158 --> 00:28:37,993
- Oh. Hello.
- Oh.

330
00:28:38,076 --> 00:28:40,370
Mom, this is Leslie.

331
00:28:40,453 --> 00:28:42,288
- Hi, Leslie.
- Hi.

332
00:28:42,330 --> 00:28:44,916
- It's nice to meet you.
- Thank you. You too.

333
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:48,502
So are you and your family
getting settled in OK?

334
00:28:48,544 --> 00:28:51,839
- Yes, ma'am.
- That's nice.

335
00:28:51,922 --> 00:28:54,424
- Come on. See ya later.
- Not too late, OK, honey?

336
00:28:55,175 --> 00:28:59,929
- Weird and weirder.
- Hey. Be glad he's found a friend.

337
00:29:00,013 --> 00:29:03,600
- Where's your dad work?
- At home. Same as my mom.

338
00:29:03,683 --> 00:29:05,685
- They're writers.
- Writers?

339
00:29:05,768 --> 00:29:08,729
- What do they write about?
- Fiction.

340
00:29:08,771 --> 00:29:10,356
That explains you.

341
00:29:11,732 --> 00:29:15,068
- What do you mean?
- Well, you like to make things up.

342
00:29:15,110 --> 00:29:17,529
And that's what your parents
do for a living.

343
00:29:18,822 --> 00:29:21,366
You know a lot about hardware?

344
00:29:21,449 --> 00:29:23,284
No. Why?

345
00:29:23,368 --> 00:29:26,746
Well, your dad works
at a hardware store.

346
00:29:26,829 --> 00:29:28,414
OK.

347
00:29:28,914 --> 00:29:31,500
All I'm saying is that
you are who you are...

348
00:29:31,583 --> 00:29:33,168
...not your parents.

349
00:29:35,587 --> 00:29:39,007
If they work at your house, you must
get to hang out with them a lot.

350
00:29:41,676 --> 00:29:43,344
Not really.

351
00:29:45,721 --> 00:29:47,390
What's that?

352
00:29:47,473 --> 00:29:50,226
- Grenade.
- There're no grenades here.

353
00:29:53,479 --> 00:29:54,605
Come on!

354
00:29:58,150 --> 00:30:01,402
- Squirrels!
- Part squirrel, part Scott Hoager.

355
00:30:01,486 --> 00:30:04,364
- Squogre.
- Squogre!

356
00:30:04,697 --> 00:30:07,158
The sneaky foot soldiers
of the Dark Master.

357
00:30:08,242 --> 00:30:10,411
- They're attacking!
- We need ammo!

358
00:30:17,834 --> 00:30:19,753
This is not good.

359
00:30:21,588 --> 00:30:24,966
- See them? Up there?
- Yeah.

360
00:30:25,049 --> 00:30:28,886
- Do you? Really?
- Yeah.

361
00:30:39,104 --> 00:30:40,355
Les...

362
00:30:41,481 --> 00:30:42,607
Leslie?

363
00:30:44,233 --> 00:30:47,403
Leslie. Leslie!

364
00:30:49,029 --> 00:30:51,490
Come on. You can see
the whole kingdom from up here.

365
00:30:54,952 --> 00:30:57,829
Isn't this cool?
We can do anything here.

366
00:31:07,129 --> 00:31:09,006
Look at it.

367
00:31:09,048 --> 00:31:11,675
It's all ours.

368
00:31:11,759 --> 00:31:15,053
From the mountains to the oceans.

369
00:31:17,889 --> 00:31:20,433
- What am I looking for exactly?
- You'll see.

370
00:31:20,517 --> 00:31:23,353
Just close your eyes...

371
00:31:23,436 --> 00:31:25,104
...but keep your mind wide open.

372
00:31:39,284 --> 00:31:40,410
Wow.

373
00:31:42,078 --> 00:31:44,038
What do we call this place?

374
00:31:46,958 --> 00:31:48,459
Terabithia.

375
00:31:54,923 --> 00:31:59,177
Shh.
Everybody tiptoe. OK, ready?

376
00:32:00,011 --> 00:32:02,305
Happy birthday!

377
00:32:16,026 --> 00:32:17,277
Make a wish.

378
00:32:18,069 --> 00:32:19,988
- Yay!
- What'd you wish for?

379
00:32:25,827 --> 00:32:29,163
- This is cheap junk.
- No, it isn't.

380
00:32:29,246 --> 00:32:31,915
- I love it.
- How? It doesn't even work.

381
00:32:31,999 --> 00:32:34,626
I don't think we have
the hang of it yet, Dad.

382
00:32:34,710 --> 00:32:37,629
You know what? Keep the box.
We'll see if we can take it back.

383
00:32:39,547 --> 00:32:41,966
Daddy, there's something
in the greenhouse.

384
00:32:47,597 --> 00:32:50,849
That's the last thing I need,
some animal chewing it's way in here.

385
00:32:51,809 --> 00:32:54,061
What are you going to do
if you catch it?

386
00:32:54,144 --> 00:32:56,355
These vegetables are our livelihood.

387
00:32:56,396 --> 00:32:59,482
Can't afford to share them
with animals that get in here.

388
00:33:00,358 --> 00:33:02,235
- So, you're gonna kill it?
- Have to.

389
00:33:04,696 --> 00:33:08,783
Well, he's not gonna
get in here now, right, Dad?

390
00:33:08,866 --> 00:33:12,369
Hope not. But if he does,
you just let me deal with it.

391
00:33:13,787 --> 00:33:15,956
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

392
00:33:16,039 --> 00:33:19,584
No, why don't you go on and do
your homework, I'll clean this mess up.

393
00:33:30,970 --> 00:33:32,888
Under the seat.

394
00:33:37,601 --> 00:33:39,686
I heard it was
your birthday yesterday.

395
00:33:43,731 --> 00:33:46,567
- Like it?
- Wow.

396
00:33:47,360 --> 00:33:49,737
It must've cost a fortune.

397
00:33:50,279 --> 00:33:52,364
What's it matter what it costs?

398
00:33:53,282 --> 00:33:54,449
I don't know.

399
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:57,828
Well, I can take it back
and get a cheaper one, if you want.

400
00:33:59,537 --> 00:34:02,373
Thanks... a lot.

401
00:34:16,845 --> 00:34:18,763
Look.
The squogre and the vulture.

402
00:34:18,847 --> 00:34:20,473
Hey, here he comes.

403
00:34:20,557 --> 00:34:23,893
And a guy who can stand up to a squogre
is scared of a Hoager?

404
00:34:26,812 --> 00:34:28,814
Ms. Edmunds?

405
00:34:28,898 --> 00:34:31,650
- He speaks.
- Can I help you with those?

406
00:34:31,734 --> 00:34:34,987
You sure can.
And you just made my day.

407
00:34:37,531 --> 00:34:38,865
- Great.
- I'll get that one.

408
00:34:38,949 --> 00:34:40,200
Thank you.

409
00:34:47,081 --> 00:34:50,000
- Hey, guys.
- Oh, hi, boys.

410
00:34:56,882 --> 00:34:59,134
How come you're so good at that?

411
00:34:59,217 --> 00:35:01,302
- Good at what?
- Building stuff.

412
00:35:01,344 --> 00:35:02,845
You're good at it for a girl.

413
00:35:02,929 --> 00:35:05,681
Same way I'm fast... for a girl.

414
00:35:05,765 --> 00:35:08,142
You know what I mean.

415
00:35:08,225 --> 00:35:11,228
You're pretty good at art... for a boy.

416
00:35:11,270 --> 00:35:13,105
OK, OK, truce.

417
00:35:17,067 --> 00:35:19,444
Don't your parents notice
this stuff's missing?

418
00:35:19,569 --> 00:35:21,821
Not when they're in
the middle of writing a book.

419
00:35:21,905 --> 00:35:24,365
What's that?

420
00:35:25,491 --> 00:35:26,617
Show yourselves!

421
00:35:39,713 --> 00:35:41,965
It's a giant troll!

422
00:35:42,048 --> 00:35:44,175
No, it's a giant tree
that almost killed us!

423
00:35:44,217 --> 00:35:46,636
You think that tree
just fell all by itself?

424
00:35:47,845 --> 00:35:48,888
Come on.

425
00:35:48,929 --> 00:35:52,224
When the Dark Master saw
the squogres weren't scaring us away,

426
00:35:52,307 --> 00:35:55,686
- he sent a giant troll.
- How big?

427
00:35:59,981 --> 00:36:01,900
That's how big its feet are.

428
00:36:05,027 --> 00:36:08,072
- You really think so?
- What else could it be?

429
00:36:09,782 --> 00:36:11,533
What should we do?

430
00:36:16,830 --> 00:36:20,500
If we had a troll hunter, we could
track its scent and sneak up on it.

431
00:36:21,251 --> 00:36:23,211
Hey, look at that! Come on!

432
00:36:25,838 --> 00:36:27,256
I think it went that way!

433
00:36:28,174 --> 00:36:31,302
We rule Terabithia,
and nothing crushes us!

434
00:36:35,931 --> 00:36:37,432
I'll race you to the rope.

435
00:36:43,271 --> 00:36:45,690
I love this place!

436
00:37:02,789 --> 00:37:05,416
Go on, get out of here.
And don't come back.

437
00:37:18,637 --> 00:37:20,555
What do you think you're doing?

438
00:37:20,638 --> 00:37:24,434
- I took care of it for you.
- Did you, now? Now, how'd you do that?

439
00:37:24,517 --> 00:37:27,270
I took him into the forest.
He's not coming back, promise.

440
00:37:27,353 --> 00:37:30,606
Did he tell you he's gonna
stay the hell out of the greenhouse?

441
00:37:30,648 --> 00:37:33,025
No, he went out there
and he's not coming...

442
00:37:33,108 --> 00:37:35,277
Jess, you need to understand
something, OK?

443
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:39,072
This is not one of your cartoons. This
is just a pest that eats up our food,

444
00:37:39,114 --> 00:37:41,199
money we earn and time we don't have.

445
00:37:42,492 --> 00:37:44,369
- OK.
- Get your head out of the clouds

446
00:37:44,410 --> 00:37:45,536
and do as I say.

447
00:37:46,495 --> 00:37:48,205
OK.

448
00:38:17,190 --> 00:38:19,025
Good night, sweetheart.

449
00:38:20,694 --> 00:38:22,237
Sweet dreams.

450
00:38:23,279 --> 00:38:26,490
Lights out, Jess.

451
00:38:26,574 --> 00:38:28,159
Night, Dad.

452
00:38:34,122 --> 00:38:36,750
Are we slaying the giant troll
after school today?

453
00:38:36,833 --> 00:38:39,461
You've got your head
in the clouds, Leslie.

454
00:38:39,544 --> 00:38:42,922
- Huh?
- There is no giant troll, all right?

455
00:38:43,006 --> 00:38:46,634
Well, you better not let
the Terabithians hear you.

456
00:38:46,717 --> 00:38:48,511
They thought you were their king.

457
00:39:02,232 --> 00:39:05,693
Alexandra, my daddy gave me Twinkies!

458
00:39:05,776 --> 00:39:08,863
Neither one squished, 'cause I
didn't put them next to my drink.

459
00:39:08,946 --> 00:39:10,698
I'd shut up about those Twinkies.

460
00:39:10,781 --> 00:39:13,450
You're just mad 'cause I
got some and you didn't.

461
00:39:13,492 --> 00:39:15,661
Whatever. Don't cry to me
when you lose them.

462
00:39:15,744 --> 00:39:17,245
I'll eat them, not lose them.

463
00:39:22,709 --> 00:39:25,419
Jess! Jess!

464
00:39:25,503 --> 00:39:29,381
Janice Avery stole my Twinkies!
Janice Avery stole my Twinkies!

465
00:39:29,465 --> 00:39:33,135
- I told you, keep your mouth shut.
- She's there. What are you gonna do?

466
00:39:33,177 --> 00:39:35,304
And she makes you pay to pee!

467
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:38,265
It's a dollar, shorty.

468
00:39:38,348 --> 00:39:41,893
But I don't have a dollar.

469
00:39:41,976 --> 00:39:45,396
That's not fair, is it?
Peeing's definitely supposed to be free.

470
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:46,731
Free to pee!

471
00:39:46,814 --> 00:39:49,900
Free to pee! Free to pee! Free to pee!

472
00:39:52,695 --> 00:39:53,737
Let's go.

473
00:40:05,706 --> 00:40:07,958
I want my Twinkies, Janice Avery.

474
00:40:08,042 --> 00:40:09,877
What Twinkies, Twinkie?

475
00:40:11,128 --> 00:40:14,256
You're supposed to beat her up.
You're my brother!

476
00:40:14,339 --> 00:40:17,342
Do you know what would happen
if I were to pick a fight with her?

477
00:40:17,426 --> 00:40:19,552
You'll get your butt kicked.

478
00:40:19,594 --> 00:40:23,389
No, I'd get kicked out of school for
fighting a girl. What's that prove?

479
00:40:23,473 --> 00:40:26,100
She stole my Twinkies.

480
00:40:27,601 --> 00:40:29,311
Come on.

481
00:40:31,105 --> 00:40:32,815
It's all right, May Belle.

482
00:40:32,898 --> 00:40:36,610
We'll get her back. Won't we, Jess?

483
00:40:40,989 --> 00:40:43,658
Don't let
the Terabithians hear you.

484
00:40:43,741 --> 00:40:45,576
They thought you were their king.

485
00:41:04,969 --> 00:41:06,929
Jess! Jess!

486
00:41:16,980 --> 00:41:20,400
Oh... Hi! Look at you!

487
00:41:20,483 --> 00:41:25,029
That is your very own, certified,
purebred, giant troll hunter.

488
00:41:25,613 --> 00:41:26,989
- He's for me?
- Yeah,

489
00:41:27,073 --> 00:41:29,366
he just took a giant
