722
00:59:47,290 --> 00:59:49,250
Great. Now there's three of us.

723
00:59:55,922 --> 00:59:58,425
- Wow.
- Now we're even.

724
00:59:58,466 --> 00:59:59,884
Attack!

725
01:00:08,684 --> 01:00:12,730
Dead meat! Dead meat!
Dead meat! Dead meat! Dead meat!

726
01:00:14,189 --> 01:00:15,148
Come on.

727
01:00:15,774 --> 01:00:19,069
- Come on, P.T.
- Dead meat!

728
01:00:40,839 --> 01:00:43,257
Be careful!
You're almost there.

729
01:00:50,222 --> 01:00:52,474
Jess!

730
01:00:52,975 --> 01:00:54,184
Jess!

731
01:01:11,742 --> 01:01:12,826
Hey.

732
01:02:00,829 --> 01:02:02,789
- See ya!
- Yeah, see ya.

733
01:02:51,333 --> 01:02:53,752
Jess! I called you three times.

734
01:02:53,836 --> 01:02:55,045
It's your girlfriend.

735
01:02:55,087 --> 01:02:57,130
She's not my girlfriend.

736
01:02:58,089 --> 01:03:00,133
- Hey.
- Hello, Jess.

737
01:03:00,216 --> 01:03:02,176
Wait. Who is this?

738
01:03:02,260 --> 01:03:04,804
It's Saturday, but it's
your teacher, Ms. Edmunds.

739
01:03:04,846 --> 01:03:09,058
I was planning on taking my nephews
into the city to the museum,

740
01:03:09,141 --> 01:03:12,853
and my sister changed her plans
last minute, so I had a thought.

741
01:03:17,149 --> 01:03:19,859
- Hey, Mom.
- Hmm? Is it the baby?

742
01:03:19,901 --> 01:03:22,569
No, she's fine.
May Belle's got her.

743
01:03:22,570 --> 01:03:25,990
Teacher wants me to go
on a field trip today.

744
01:03:26,073 --> 01:03:28,743
- Is that OK?
- Mmm.

745
01:03:32,871 --> 01:03:34,706
Ms. Edmunds? Yeah, I can go.

746
01:03:42,630 --> 01:03:44,298
- All set?
- Yeah.

747
01:03:44,340 --> 01:03:45,716
- Yeah?
- Yes, ma'am.

748
01:03:52,681 --> 01:03:54,558
Forget something?

749
01:03:56,435 --> 01:03:58,687
No. I'm good.

750
01:04:33,385 --> 01:04:35,012
Wow.

751
01:04:40,141 --> 01:04:41,768
Honey, honey, stay here.

752
01:04:44,812 --> 01:04:47,315
- Do you like it?
- Yeah.

753
01:04:47,398 --> 01:04:50,359
It's Brueghel.
It's one of my favorites.

754
01:04:50,442 --> 01:04:53,612
I wonder if he started in notebooks
like you. I know da Vinci did.

755
01:04:58,283 --> 01:05:01,244
It's amazing how much
detail's put into it.

756
01:05:01,327 --> 01:05:03,538
You've been to a museum before, right?

757
01:05:03,579 --> 01:05:06,916
- No, it's my first time.
- Really?

758
01:05:06,958 --> 01:05:09,585
- Yup.
- Well, then I'm honored.

759
01:05:47,536 --> 01:05:49,329
It's such a nice day out.

760
01:05:49,330 --> 01:05:53,458
It's been raining so much, I began
to think it was like that Japanese myth

761
01:05:53,542 --> 01:05:57,379
where the sun goes into the cave
and vows never to come out.

762
01:05:57,462 --> 01:06:00,548
- You know about everything.
- Not by a long shot.

763
01:06:00,632 --> 01:06:02,550
But I do try to keep an open mind,

764
01:06:02,634 --> 01:06:05,094
and you'd be surprised
what finds its way in there.

765
01:06:05,178 --> 01:06:08,722
That's what Leslie Burke says.
She told me to keep my mind wide open.

766
01:06:08,806 --> 01:06:10,391
Leslie Burke is right.

767
01:06:10,432 --> 01:06:13,936
Mind like yours wide open,
you could create a whole new world.

768
01:06:21,526 --> 01:06:25,238
- Thank you very much.
- You're very welcome.

769
01:06:25,321 --> 01:06:28,783
- Maybe we could do this again sometime.
- Absolutely.

770
01:06:33,370 --> 01:06:35,747
- Hey, guys.
- See? I told you.

771
01:06:35,831 --> 01:06:37,791
Oh, my God, Jess!

772
01:06:39,376 --> 01:06:42,545
- Where in God's name have you been?
- Where have you been?

773
01:06:43,671 --> 01:06:45,923
Mom...

774
01:06:45,965 --> 01:06:48,342
I asked you. It wasn't like I...

775
01:06:48,426 --> 01:06:51,011
- They thought you were dead.
- Brenda, hush.

776
01:06:51,053 --> 01:06:52,846
Dead?

777
01:06:53,931 --> 01:06:55,682
What's going on?

778
01:07:02,146 --> 01:07:04,482
Your friend Leslie's dead.

779
01:07:06,234 --> 01:07:07,985
She drowned in a creek this morning.

780
01:07:08,027 --> 01:07:11,530
Apparently she tried to swing
across on a rope and it broke.

781
01:07:11,572 --> 01:07:13,740
They think she hit her head.

782
01:07:15,492 --> 01:07:18,828
No... No, it's not that kind of rope.

783
01:07:18,912 --> 01:07:22,373
It couldn't break.
It... wouldn't have.

784
01:07:22,415 --> 01:07:24,375
But it did.

785
01:07:27,545 --> 01:07:31,048
- I'm sorry, son.
- No, you're lying.

786
01:07:31,882 --> 01:07:35,761
- She's not even dead. You're lying!
- Jess!

787
01:09:06,177 --> 01:09:09,305
Hi, honey. You want some breakfast?

788
01:09:09,388 --> 01:09:12,015
I... I gotta do my chores first.

789
01:09:12,099 --> 01:09:14,768
Your dad's doing everything today.
You just sit down.

790
01:09:30,115 --> 01:09:31,825
Jess, your father and I thought

791
01:09:31,867 --> 01:09:34,411
we'd go to the Burkes today
and pay our respects.

792
01:09:34,494 --> 01:09:36,747
Just the three of us.

793
01:09:37,747 --> 01:09:39,124
Paying what?

794
01:09:59,726 --> 01:10:01,394
Prince Terrien. Shh.

795
01:10:02,270 --> 01:10:04,105
You must be Jess.

796
01:10:12,946 --> 01:10:17,450
I'm Mr. Aarons. This is my wife, Mary.
Very sorry about your loss.

797
01:10:17,534 --> 01:10:19,994
- I'm so sorry.
- Hi, Jess.

798
01:10:27,668 --> 01:10:29,587
She loved you, you know.

799
01:10:30,546 --> 01:10:32,005
You know, Leslie,

800
01:10:32,047 --> 01:10:35,842
she never had much luck
making friends at her old school.

801
01:10:35,926 --> 01:10:39,095
We were hoping that when
we moved out here she would...

802
01:10:43,182 --> 01:10:45,518
She said
if it wasn't for you...

803
01:10:47,812 --> 01:10:49,980
You're the best friend she's ever had.

804
01:10:50,064 --> 01:10:51,940
I wanna thank you for that.

805
01:10:53,400 --> 01:10:55,360
You're welcome.

806
01:10:58,363 --> 01:11:01,241
My wife and I were wondering
about the service.

807
01:11:04,619 --> 01:11:08,080
We've decided to bring Leslie
back home until the service.

808
01:11:13,585 --> 01:11:17,422
- Jess.
- Next time,

809
01:11:17,464 --> 01:11:20,341
we should invite Leslie to go.

810
01:11:22,135 --> 01:11:24,262
She'd like that.

811
01:11:33,353 --> 01:11:34,813
Hey, kid.

812
01:11:36,189 --> 01:11:38,275
Sorry about your friend.

813
01:11:40,652 --> 01:11:44,989
The purpose
of object pronouns...

814
01:11:45,072 --> 01:11:48,075
So looks like you're
the fastest kid in the class now, huh?

815
01:11:50,369 --> 01:11:52,371
It's a joke, dude.

816
01:11:56,750 --> 01:11:58,710
- Are you nuts?
- Jess Aarons.

817
01:11:59,252 --> 01:12:01,254
Go wait for me out in the hall.

818
01:12:02,672 --> 01:12:05,007
Silent reading until I get back.

819
01:12:13,974 --> 01:12:15,684
Jess...

820
01:12:22,065 --> 01:12:24,817
When my husband died...

821
01:12:24,901 --> 01:12:27,778
...people kept telling me not to cry.

822
01:12:28,821 --> 01:12:31,156
People kept trying to help me to forget.

823
01:12:34,326 --> 01:12:36,536
But I didn't wanna forget.

824
01:12:36,620 --> 01:12:38,872
Excuse me.

825
01:12:41,499 --> 01:12:44,001
The things that girl came up with.

826
01:12:45,962 --> 01:12:48,464
I don't get students like her too often.

827
01:12:52,843 --> 01:12:55,220
So I realize...

828
01:12:55,262 --> 01:12:57,889
...that if it's hard for me...

829
01:12:57,931 --> 01:13:00,392
...how much harder it must be for you.

830
01:13:46,058 --> 01:13:48,144
Hurry up.
We're gonna miss the bus!

831
01:13:57,152 --> 01:13:58,820
Hey.

832
01:14:44,070 --> 01:14:46,072
Leslie?!

833
01:15:09,802 --> 01:15:11,845
Jess!

834
01:15:11,887 --> 01:15:13,347
Leslie!

835
01:15:13,430 --> 01:15:16,725
- Jess!
- Leslie!

836
01:15:22,897 --> 01:15:24,482
Lesl...

837
01:15:24,565 --> 01:15:27,443
Help me, I can't get across! Hurry!

838
01:15:28,611 --> 01:15:30,487
May Belle?

839
01:15:32,823 --> 01:15:34,908
Hold on! Don't move!

840
01:15:36,493 --> 01:15:38,870
Here, grab my arm.
I got you, don't worry.

841
01:15:44,042 --> 01:15:46,460
- What were you thinking?
- I was worried about you!

842
01:15:46,544 --> 01:15:49,213
Well, don't be. I don't want you here!

843
01:15:49,797 --> 01:15:52,508
- But I wanna come with you.
- This is our place. Go home.

844
01:15:52,549 --> 01:15:54,343
This is our place!

845
01:15:58,305 --> 01:15:59,639
I said go home!

846
01:16:14,111 --> 01:16:15,904
Honey, what's the matter?

847
01:16:16,822 --> 01:16:18,740
What's the matter?

848
01:16:18,782 --> 01:16:20,658
What's the matter, baby?

849
01:17:22,674 --> 01:17:24,342
No!

850
01:17:25,843 --> 01:17:27,511
Jess!

851
01:17:28,471 --> 01:17:31,098
It's OK, Jess.
It's OK, son, it's OK.

852
01:17:31,181 --> 01:17:32,891
It's all gone.

853
01:17:36,228 --> 01:17:38,605
Is it like the Bible says?

854
01:17:38,688 --> 01:17:40,523
Is she going to hell?

855
01:17:41,149 --> 01:17:42,900
I don't know everything about God,

856
01:17:42,942 --> 01:17:45,695
but I do know He's not
gonna send that little girl to hell.

857
01:17:45,778 --> 01:17:48,989
Then I'm going to hell
because it's all my fault.

858
01:17:49,073 --> 01:17:52,618
Don't you think that even for a minute.

859
01:17:52,659 --> 01:17:55,203
But it is.

860
01:17:55,287 --> 01:17:59,332
I didn't invite her
to go to the museum with me.

861
01:17:59,374 --> 01:18:02,585
I didn't wanna invite her.

862
01:18:02,669 --> 01:18:05,838
I wasn't there to go with her.

863
01:18:05,922 --> 01:18:08,924
- It's my fault.
- No, no, no, no.

864
01:18:09,008 --> 01:18:11,010
It's not your fault.

865
01:18:11,093 --> 01:18:13,637
None of that makes it so.

866
01:18:13,720 --> 01:18:15,847
It's a terrible thing.

867
01:18:15,889 --> 01:18:20,310
It doesn't make any sense,
but it's not your fault, Jess.

868
01:18:25,148 --> 01:18:28,651
She brought you something special
when she came here, didn't she?

869
01:18:31,695 --> 01:18:34,031
That's what you hold on to.

870
01:18:36,992 --> 01:18:39,369
That's how you keep her alive.

871
01:18:58,803 --> 01:19:00,055
May Belle?

872
01:19:08,479 --> 01:19:09,772
Look.

873
01:19:11,523 --> 01:19:13,317
I'm sorry I pushed you.

874
01:19:15,402 --> 01:19:18,530
That was stupid and wrong...

875
01:19:20,532 --> 01:19:22,533
...and I really miss you talking to me.

876
01:20:01,319 --> 01:20:03,654
She's in your hands now.

877
01:20:25,967 --> 01:20:27,009
Hey!

878
01:20:28,844 --> 01:20:30,012
Wait!

879
01:20:32,014 --> 01:20:32,973
Wait!

880
01:20:35,225 --> 01:20:36,560
Hey!

881
01:20:42,273 --> 01:20:45,193
Jess? I'm sorry.
I didn't... I didn't see you.

882
01:20:45,276 --> 01:20:48,863
Can I use the lumber by your house?

883
01:20:48,946 --> 01:20:50,572
Yeah, yeah. Of course.

884
01:20:50,614 --> 01:20:53,283
Anything you see, you just...

885
01:20:54,117 --> 01:20:57,329
You know, I meant to...
I meant to give you Prince Terrien,

886
01:20:57,370 --> 01:21:00,498
but I... can't seem to give him up.

887
01:21:02,250 --> 01:21:04,210
Leslie would've wanted you to have him.

888
01:21:04,293 --> 01:21:05,795
Yeah.

889
01:22:25,868 --> 01:22:29,121
We're playing. By ourselves.

890
01:22:30,581 --> 01:22:34,376
OK, but I know the most
incredible place to play.

891
01:22:34,418 --> 01:22:37,379
You gotta promise you're
not gonna tell anybody about it.

892
01:22:37,462 --> 01:22:41,424
Not Brenda, not Ellie, not even Joycie.

893
01:22:41,466 --> 01:22:44,969
Tell Joycie a secret between you and me?

894
01:22:45,011 --> 01:22:46,470
She's nothing but a baby.

895
01:22:46,554 --> 01:22:49,682
You're right, and she's not ready
to be a princess yet.

896
01:22:49,765 --> 01:22:51,558
You have to train her and stuff.

897
01:22:51,600 --> 01:22:54,519
Princess? Who gets to be the princess?

898
01:23:03,861 --> 01:23:05,530
Step down.

899
01:23:08,866 --> 01:23:10,242
Watch your step.

900
01:23:17,457 --> 01:23:19,209
You're not peeking, are you?

901
01:23:21,211 --> 01:23:23,880
Step up. There you go.

902
01:23:30,970 --> 01:23:32,721
All right.

903
01:23:38,893 --> 01:23:40,770
OK. Open them.

904
01:23:46,317 --> 01:23:50,237
Wow. Did you make this?

905
01:23:51,572 --> 01:23:53,240
Yep.

906
01:23:55,951 --> 01:23:57,661
Hold on a second.

907
01:24:06,002 --> 01:24:09,213
Look! They must've heard the rumor,

908
01:24:09,296 --> 01:24:13,884
that the beautiful girl arriving today
is the new future ruler of Terabithia.

909
01:24:13,967 --> 01:24:17,137
- Who heard?
- The Terabithians.

910
01:24:17,179 --> 01:24:19,389
They've been waiting.

911
01:24:19,431 --> 01:24:21,349
Where?

912
01:24:21,432 --> 01:24:24,769
- I don't see them.
- It's an ancient forest, May Belle,

913
01:24:24,811 --> 01:24:27,104
full of magical creatures
and friendly giants,

914
01:24:27,188 --> 01:24:29,398
anything you can imagine.

915
01:24:29,481 --> 01:24:31,358
But you gotta look really hard.

916
01:24:31,400 --> 01:24:34,194
But keep your mind wide open.

917
01:24:42,452 --> 01:24:44,245
So, what do you think?

918
01:24:48,457 --> 01:24:50,793
Can there be purple flowers?

919
01:24:52,836 --> 01:24:55,130
Anything you want.

920
01:24:56,089 --> 01:24:58,008
Wow.

921
01:24:59,342 --> 01:25:00,593
And a castle.

922
01:25:00,677 --> 01:25:03,346
A big one, with towers and flags.

923
01:25:03,388 --> 01:25:05,640
Of course.

924
01:25:08,350 --> 01:25:11,061
Look, Jess. It's beautiful.

925
01:25:14,773 --> 01:25:16,441
Is there a king?

926
01:25:16,525 --> 01:25:17,859
Are you the king, Jess?

927
01:25:17,943 --> 01:25:20,445
Only if you're princess.

928
01:26:04,152 --> 01:26:06,445
Terabithia.